      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-level2",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys 2022R2, DePuy Synthes internal) are commercial or agency-validated solvers with documented version control, regression test suites, and change-control records. SQA documentation reviewed and confirmed compliant with Gradation 2 requirements. No open non-conformances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/ncv-level2",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 and solver vendor verification suites were executed for each code. Results matched analytical solutions within numerical precision tolerances. Patch test and single-element tests confirmed element formulation correctness for hexahedral and tetrahedral elements used in the pedicle screw models."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/disc-error-level3",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh convergence study conducted across three refinement levels (coarse ~120k elements, medium ~380k elements, fine ~950k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) < 2% for all QoIs at the medium mesh, which was selected for production runs. Contact region mesh sensitivity separately verified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residual norms (tolerance 1e-5). Iterative solver (sparse direct LU) confirmed stable across all load steps. No divergence or ill-conditioning detected. Energy balance checked at each increment; artificial energy < 0.1% of total strain energy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review performed for all three modeling groups. Boundary conditions, load application, and material assignments cross-checked against ASTM F1717 protocol and device geometry specifications. No discrepancies identified. Simulation inputs traceable to approved model documentation packages."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level3",
      "rationale": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model (isotropic hardening, von Mises yield) selected based on material characterization data for Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.2) used at screw-block interfaces, consistent with literature and preliminary experimental friction measurements. Model form uncertainty estimated via sensitivity to friction coefficient (±0.05) and hardening modulus (±5%); QoI sensitivity within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "Material properties (elastic modulus, yield strength, ultimate strength) sourced from device manufacturer coupon testing (N=5 coupons per lot). However, only a single material lot was characterized, and inter-lot variability was not quantified. Geometric inputs derived from nominal CAD with no as-built dimensional verification against the tested specimens. These gaps prevent achievement of required Gradation 3 for model inputs. Remediation requires multi-lot material characterization and as-built geometry measurements for at least a subset of test specimens."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-level3",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH Biomedical Physics Branch and DePuy Synthes test facility). Specimens drawn from production lots with full traceability. Sample size supports statistical comparison metrics. Inter-laboratory variability characterized; coefficient of variation < 5% for stiffness and yield force across labs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level3",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single set of ASTM F1717 conditions (5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature, standard UHMWPE block geometry). No variation in test speed, temperature, or block stiffness was explored. The COU requires confidence across the clinical loading envelope, but the single test condition does not support extrapolation. This factor is substantially below the required Gradation 3. Remediation requires testing at minimum two additional load rates and one elevated temperature condition representative of sterilization-exposed implants."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions mapped directly to ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry and loading protocol. Block stiffness, screw insertion depth, and rod connector geometry confirmed consistent between physical test setup and FEA model. Correspondence table documenting parameter equivalency reviewed and approved by all three modeling teams."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "QoI differences computed for stiffness (FEA 6.8% above mean experimental), yield force (FEA 11.3% above mean experimental — exceeds the pre-established <10% bound), and force at 40 mm displacement (FEA within 7.2%). The E/uval metric for yield force is 2.14, exceeding the acceptance threshold of 1.96. Although stiffness and displacement force pass acceptance criteria, yield force failure prevents a passing output comparison assessment. Gradation 3 requires all primary QoIs within acceptance bounds; achieved level is 2 (partial agreement). Remediation requires model calibration or expanded uncertainty budget justification for yield force."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the regulatory QoIs used in 510(k) substantial equivalence comparisons. Clinical relevance established by published biomechanical literature linking construct stiffness and yield force to fusion success and hardware failure risk. QoI selection reviewed and endorsed by clinical advisory panel."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/val-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the COU: the same device (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), same test standard (ASTM F1717), same loading mode (static compression-bending), and same QoIs. Multi-laboratory design strengthens generalizability. Validation scenario mapping document confirms high fidelity between validation conditions and intended regulatory submission context."
    }
