  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) is NOT ACCEPTED based on three factors that fail to meet required credibility levels: (1) Model inputs [achieved 2, required 3]: Material property characterization is limited to a single production lot with no inter-lot variability data, and as-built geometry of tested specimens was not measured, preventing adequate characterization of input uncertainty. (2) Test conditions [achieved 1, required 3]: Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 condition with no exploration of load rate, temperature, or fixture variation. The single-condition dataset does not support the breadth of confidence required for the COU. This is the most critical deficiency. (3) Output comparison [achieved 2, required 3]: The yield force QoI shows a 11.3% mean difference (exceeding the pre-established <10% acceptance bound) and an E/uval of 2.14 (exceeding the 1.96 threshold), indicating that the model does not adequately reproduce this primary regulatory QoI within the agreed acceptance criteria. The remaining ten factors meet or exceed their required levels. Remediation path: (a) conduct multi-lot material characterization (minimum 3 lots, N≥5 coupons per lot) and as-built dimensional inspection of a representative specimen subset; (b) expand testing to minimum three load rate conditions and one elevated-temperature condition; (c) investigate and resolve yield force discrepancy through model sensitivity analysis, potential recalibration of contact friction or plasticity parameters, or justified expansion of the validation uncertainty budget with independent evidence. Resubmission for credibility assessment is encouraged once remediation activities are documented.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
